I also saw a similar problem while experimenting with an Atmel microcontroller
and a Futuba servo. My problem ended up being that I had forgotten to have a
common ground between the controller and the servo. Once I connected the grounds
everything worked like a charm.

Mike


>I've had a similar problem, make sure your servo power is fully charged.  An

>undercharged system will sometimes drive all the way one way.
